# Refactoring Standards

## Mikado Method (6 Phases)
1. Define the refactoring goal
2. Attempt the change
3. If tests break, note the failure
4. Trace to root cause
5. Fix root cause first (smallest possible change)
6. Retry the goal

## Safety Rules
- Never refactor and add features in the same commit
- Run full verify before and after refactoring
- Keep a refactoring log in the PR description
- If a refactoring touches >5 files, create a plan first

## Patterns
- Extract method/class for duplicated logic
- Replace magic numbers with named constants
- Introduce interfaces for external dependencies
- Use the Strangler Fig pattern for large rewrites
